<doc>
  <member name="D3D10_TEX2DMS_ARRAY_DSV">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies the <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-types">subresource(s)</a> from an array of multisampled <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-types">2D textures</a> for a depth-stencil view.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>This structure is one member of a depth-stencil-view description (see <see cref="D3D10_DEPTH_STENCIL_VIEW_DESC" />).</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-reference-resource-structures">Resource Structures</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_TEX2DMS_ARRAY_DSV.FirstArraySlice">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>The index of the first texture to use in an array of textures (see <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d10/d3d10-graphics-programming-guide-resources-types">array slice</a>)</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D10_TEX2DMS_ARRAY_DSV.ArraySize">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">UINT</a></b></para>
      <para>Number of textures to use.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>